headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 29 points, Payton Pritchard had 22 points on six 3-pointers and the Boston Celtics beat the Charlotte Hornets 113-103 for the second straight night at the Spectrum Center on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 29 points, Celtics beat Hornets 113-103 to sweep back-to-back in Charlotte

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. scored 27 points and the Memphis Grizzlies rolled to a 124-107 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jaren Jackson Jr. scores 27 points in the Grizzlies' 124-107 victory over the 76ers

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 31 points, Chris Boucher had a season-high 24, and the Toronto Raptors snapped a four-game losing streak by beating the Sacramento Kings 131-128 in overtime on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores 31, Boucher has season-high 24 in Raptors' 131-128 overtime win over Kings

video.headline: Kings fall in OT thriller to Raptors

highlights.headline: Kings fall in OT thriller to Raptors
highlights.description: Kings come up just short in overtime missing clutch shots and falling to the Raptors 131-128 with their three-game winning streak coming to an end.

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 27 points and the Golden State Warriors squandered a huge lead before outlasting the Houston Rockets 127-121 in overtime Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield scores 27 points, Warriors outlast Rockets 127-121 in OT after squandering big lead

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 30 points including a jumper with three-tenths of a second left and the Cleveland Cavaliers remained unbeaten with a 114-113 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell's last-second jumper helps Cavs stay unbeaten with 114-113 win at Milwaukee

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Keldon Johnson had 25 points, Chris Paul added 15 points and 13 assists, and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 113-103 on Saturday night without coach Gregg Popovich, who missed the game due to illness.
headlines.shortLinkText: Johnson and Paul lead Spurs past Timberwolves 113-103 as Popovich misses game with illness

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 20 of his 32 points in the first half and the Miami Heat beat the Washington Wizards 118-98 on Saturday night in the 14th NBA regular-season game in Mexico.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam Adebayo scores 32 points to help the Heat beat the Wizards, 118-98 in Mexico City

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 27 points and Michael Porter Jr. had 20 as the Denver Nuggets used a third-quarter offensive surge to beat the Utah Jazz 129-103 on Saturday night for their first home win of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic scores team-high 27 points, leading the Nuggets past the Jazz 129-103

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker had 28 points, nine rebounds and nine assists, and the Phoenix Suns used a dominant third quarter beat the Portland Trail Blazers 103-97 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 28, Durant has 21 as Suns down Trail Blazers 103-97
